<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-555-640  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 555 640.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  August 21 1989 n552 p8(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Unisys: 8% staff cut: wants to cut costs by $400 million.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ryan, Margaret.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Unisys announces its intention to reduce its worldwide work forceby eight percent as part of a program aimed at cutting operatingcosts by $400 million.andP;  The program is expected to result inimproved market position and profitability when it is completed byDec 1990.andP;  The company cited permanent alterations of theirproduct mix, changes in manufacturing technology and a reductionin the overall growth rate for the computer industry as reasonsfor the austerity program.andP;  Other reasons cited for the poorperformance of the company include excessive inventory and sharpcompetition in the industry.andP;  In addition to reducing its88,000-strong work force, Unisys will restructure its USoperations with the aim of reducing overhead and sharpening itstechnical support and marketing functions for its Unix, CTOS/BTOSand microcomputer product lines.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Unisys Corp. (planning).andO;Ticker:    UIS.andO;Topic:     Strategic PlanningLayoffCost ReductionManagement.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>